-- North Korea Names Hyon Yong Chol Vice Marshal of Army
-- B y   S t e v e n   M c P h e r s o n
-- 2012-07-16T21:01:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-16/north-korea-names-hyon-yong-chol-vice-marshal-of-army.html
North Korea  named Hyon Yong Chol to
the position of vice marshal of the Korean People’s Army,
according to the North’s official Korea Central News Agency.  The decision was made Monday by the Central Military
Commission of the Workers’ Party and the National Defense
Commission, KCNA said in a two paragraph statement.  The appointment comes a day after North Korea announced it
had dismissed military chief Ri Yong Ho.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven McPherson at 
 smcpherson@bloomberg.net  